Environmental Expert Product Safety&nbsp;-&nbsp;(18019326)&nbsp;
<h2>Description</h2>&nbsp;
<p><b>Syngenta</b> is leading science-based agtech company; dedicated to bringing plant potential to life. Each of our 28,000 employees in more than 90 countries work together to solve one of humanity’s most pressing challenges: growing more food with fewer resources. A diverse workforce and an inclusive workplace environment are enablers of our ambition to be the most collaborative and trusted team in agriculture.</p>
<p>Our employees reflect the diversity of our customers, the markets where we operate and the communities which we serve. No matter what your position, you will have a vital role in safely feeding the world and taking care of our planet. Join us and help shape the future of agriculture.</p>&nbsp;
<b>Purpose statement:</b>&nbsp;
<p>Environmental Safety is a global organization with teams based across multiple countries in three continents and is responsible for ensuring that Syngenta's chemical and seeds technologies are safe for the environment. These teams focus on supporting the development of novel, safe pesticides and are responsible for ensuring that the range of chemical and seeds products marketed by Syngenta comply with rigorous internal standards for environmental safety. In addition, environmental safety teams ensure compliance with often-complex risk assessments required by public bodies, e.g. the European Food Safety Authority, for active ingredient and product registrations. This requires that data supporting our understanding of the safety and the registrations of products regionally and globally is generated to the highest standards.</p>&nbsp;
<p>At present, multiple positions are open for ecotoxicologists, environmental fate experts and environmental risk assessors. Whether you are a young professional looking to take your first steps in industry or a seasoned expert, we invite you to apply.</p>&nbsp;
<h2>Qualifications</h2>&nbsp;
<b>What we are looking for:</b>
<ul>
 <li>Background in biological science or chemistry preferably with a higher degree level (MSc or PhD)</li>
 <li>Strong project management skills with the ability to work on multiple projects in parallel</li>
 <li>A passion to solve challenging scientific questions</li>
 <li>Well-refined communication skills</li>
 <li>Purpose-driven individuals who recognize the strength of working in teams</li>
 <li>Perseverance during times of adversity</li>
</ul>&nbsp;
<b>What we offer:</b>
<ul>
 <li>Exciting opportunities to work in the disciplines of ecotoxicology, risk assessment and environmental fate</li>
 <li>Become part of a global team of over 300 experts</li>
 <li>Work in multi-disciplinary teams with colleagues from Research and Development and with scientists in our partner organizations, including universities and contract research organizations</li>
 <li>Work in a dynamic environment where regulations change and constantly challenge our ways of thinking</li>
 <li>The opportunity to approach scientific challenges with an entrepreneurial mindset</li>
 <li>Continuous learning experience and growth opportunities in an international company</li>
 <li>Opportunities to work in our main locations in the UK, the US or Switzerland, or flexibly in another country connected to one of the local teams.</li>
 <li>Work flexibly (local office, flexible working hours) based on level of experience</li>
</ul>&nbsp;
